  "prompt": "What towns are located near the Kilauea, and how does this volcano's activity compare to other volcanoes in the Pacific?",
  "response": "Kilauea is located on the island of Hawaii (Big Island) in Hawaii Volcanoes National Park. Some nearby towns include:\n\n1. Volcano Village (directly adjacent to the national park)\n2. Pahoa\n3. Hilo (largest nearby city, about 30 miles away)\n4. Hawaiian Paradise Park\n5. Kapoho (partially destroyed by the 2018 eruption)\n\nCompared to other Pacific volcanoes, Kilauea is notably:\n- One of the world's most active volcanoes\n- Continuously erupting from 1983-2018\n- Experienced a major eruption in 2018 that destroyed over 700 homes\n- Part of the Hawaiian volcanic chain, which is different from subduction zone volcanoes\n- Characterized by shield volcano structure with mostly effusive (flowing lava) eruptions\n- Generally less explosive than Pacific Rim volcanoes like those in Japan or Indonesia\n\nKilauea is unique for its relatively consistent and predictable volcanic activity, making it a significant site for volcanic research and observation.",
